{"questionId":"9272","questionHtml":"<div class=\"qb-parent-stem\"><p>The functions <span class=\"mjpage\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\"f\">\n  <mi>f</mi>\n</math></span> and <span class=\"mjpage\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\"g\">\n  <mi>g</mi>\n</math></span> are defined such that&nbsp;<span class=\"mjpage\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\"f\\left( x \\right) = \\frac{{x + 3}}{4}\">\n  <mi>f</mi>\n  <mrow>\n    <mo>(</mo>\n    <mi>x</mi>\n    <mo>)</mo>\n  </mrow>\n  <mo>=</mo>\n  <mfrac>\n    <mrow>\n      <mi>x</mi>\n      <mo>+</mo>\n      <mn>3</mn>\n    </mrow>\n    <mn>4</mn>\n  </mfrac>\n</math></span> and&nbsp;<span class=\"mjpage\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\"g\\left( x \\right) = 8x + 5\">\n  <mi>g</mi>\n  <mrow>\n    <mo>(</mo>\n    <mi>x</mi>\n    <mo>)</mo>\n  </mrow>\n  <mo>=</mo>\n  <mn>8</mn>\n  <mi>x</mi>\n  <mo>+</mo>\n  <mn>5</mn>\n</math></span>.</p></div>\n<div class=\"qb-leaf-prompt\"><p>Show that <span class=\"mjpage\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\"\\left( {g \\circ f} \\right)\\left( x \\right) = 2x + 11\">\n  <mrow>\n    <mo>(</mo>\n    <mrow>\n      <mi>g</mi>\n      <mo>∘</mo>\n      <mi>f</mi>\n    </mrow>\n    <mo>)</mo>\n  </mrow>\n  <mrow>\n    <mo>(</mo>\n    <mi>x</mi>\n    <mo>)</mo>\n  </mrow>\n  <mo>=</mo>\n  <mn>2</mn>\n  <mi>x</mi>\n  <mo>+</mo>\n  <mn>11</mn>\n</math></span>.</p></div>","markschemeHtml":"<p>attempt to form composition&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;<em><strong>M1</strong></em></p>\n<p>correct substitution&nbsp;<span class=\"mjpage\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\"g\\left( {\\frac{{x + 3}}{4}} \\right) = 8\\left( {\\frac{{x + 3}}{4}} \\right) + 5\">\n  <mi>g</mi>\n  <mrow>\n    <mo>(</mo>\n    <mrow>\n      <mfrac>\n        <mrow>\n          <mi>x</mi>\n          <mo>+</mo>\n          <mn>3</mn>\n        </mrow>\n        <mn>4</mn>\n      </mfrac>\n    </mrow>\n    <mo>)</mo>\n  </mrow>\n  <mo>=</mo>\n  <mn>8</mn>\n  <mrow>\n    <mo>(</mo>\n    <mrow>\n      <mfrac>\n        <mrow>\n          <mi>x</mi>\n          <mo>+</mo>\n          <mn>3</mn>\n        </mrow>\n        <mn>4</mn>\n      </mfrac>\n    </mrow>\n    <mo>)</mo>\n  </mrow>\n  <mo>+</mo>\n  <mn>5</mn>\n</math></span>&nbsp; &nbsp; <em><strong>A1</strong></em></p>\n<p><span class=\"mjpage\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\"\\left( {g \\circ f} \\right)\\left( x \\right) = 2x + 11\">\n  <mrow>\n    <mo>(</mo>\n    <mrow>\n      <mi>g</mi>\n      <mo>∘</mo>\n      <mi>f</mi>\n    </mrow>\n    <mo>)</mo>\n  </mrow>\n  <mrow>\n    <mo>(</mo>\n    <mi>x</mi>\n    <mo>)</mo>\n  </mrow>\n  <mo>=</mo>\n  <mn>2</mn>\n  <mi>x</mi>\n  <mo>+</mo>\n  <mn>11</mn>\n</math></span>&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;<em><strong>AG</strong></em></p>\n<p><em><strong>[2 marks]</strong></em></p>","meta":{"questionId":"9272","referenceCode":"SPM.1.SL.TZ0.5a","subjectId":"50-dp-mathematics-analysis-and-approaches","title":"Show that ( g ∘ f ) ( x ) = 2 x + 11 .","paper":"1","level":"SL","questionNumber":"a","marksAvailable":"[Maximum mark: 2]","breadcrumbLabels":["Topic 2—Functions","Topic 2—Functions","SL 2.5—Composite functions, identity, finding inverse"],"memberSectionIds":[],"sectionOrders":{}},"schemaVersion":2}